00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
today we are going to make lauki ki sabzi (bottlegourd vegetable)

00:00:21.820 --> 00:00:23.820
here are the ingredients we need

00:00:25.180 --> 00:00:28.100
3-4 tbsp clarified butter

00:00:30.480 --> 00:00:35.000
500 grams bottlegourd, peeled &amp; chopped and kept in water to prevent discoloring. Ensure bottlegourd is not bitter before preparing by biting into a piece. do not prepare bitter tasting bottlegourd

00:00:35.960 --> 00:00:37.500
1 medium sized onion, chopped

00:00:38.160 --> 00:00:40.160
2 tomatoes, chopped &amp; 1 green chilli, finely chopped

00:00:41.040 --> 00:00:43.040
2-3 tsp cilantro, chopped

00:00:43.340 --> 00:00:45.000
1 tsp salt

00:00:45.040 --> 00:00:47.040
1/2 tsp red chilli powder

00:00:48.700 --> 00:00:51.700
1/2 tsp turmeric powder

00:00:53.440 --> 00:00:55.440
1/2 tsp garam masala

00:00:56.540 --> 00:00:58.540
1/2 tsp coriander powder

00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:01.900
1 large mug/glass of water

00:01:02.600 --> 00:01:06.680
add oil in pressure cooker &amp; keep it on medium heat

00:01:07.640 --> 00:01:09.640
let the oil heat up

00:01:17.600 --> 00:01:30.600
then add chopped onions &amp; saute till light pink. stir continuously

00:01:31.900 --> 00:01:36.900
add the chopped tomatoes &amp; green chilli

00:01:38.000 --> 00:02:09.000
stir a few times and add the coriander powder, garam masala, turmeric powder, red chilli powder &amp; salt

00:02:10.820 --> 00:02:18.800
stir cook till the tomatoes turn soft

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:25.300
tomatoes have turned soft add the chopped bottlegourd

00:02:26.600 --> 00:02:48.600
stir roast this for 2-3 minutes to mix well with the masala

00:03:02.960 --> 00:03:18.900
add 2 tsp cilantro and mix for about a minute

00:03:31.240 --> 00:03:55.200
then add water, stir well &amp; close the cooker. keep heat on medium

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:09.500
at the first whistle reduce heat to low and cook for 15 minutes. then put off the heat

00:04:10.420 --> 00:04:15.400
open cooker when the pressure inside it subsides

00:04:18.800 --> 00:04:26.000
the bottlegourd should be soft now but there is some water. this needs to be dried

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:48.000
keep heat on medium and let simmer. if you like a little gravy in the bottlegourd then you may not dry it completely

00:04:49.000 --> 00:04:55.500
now the water has dried up completely. check salt &amp; add if less &amp; mix well. our bottlegourd vegetable is ready

00:04:55.700 --> 00:05:05.800
we will transfer our lauki ki sabzi to a serving bowl &amp; garnish it with the remaining cilantro

00:05:05.900 --> 00:05:18.800
do try this lauki ki sabzi (bottlegourd vegetable) &amp; give us your feedback. thanks for watching &amp; do subscribe to our channel.

